<h1>An Overview on Configuration Manager</h1>

<p>The <span class="UI_COMMAND" id="MenuBar_Empty_Tools.msg+MenuBar_Empty_Tools+7276">Configuration Manager</span> is a managing tool that helps you to save and restore a program configuration.</p>

<p>The program allows you to perform the following tasks:</p>

<ul>
<li>Centralized management of the program configuration settings for multiple installations.</li>

<li>Import or export configuration settings between machines.</li>

<li>Maintain the same configuration settings through different installations of product version.</li>

<li>Store the customizations among the user data, which can be easily shared with other users.</li>
</ul>

<p>The configuration is a collection of the program parameters. The program parameters are stored in files or registration keys.</p>

<p>You can select the specific parameters from a list of available settings and specify the name of the new configuration. A saved configuration can be loaded from another machine, thereby avoiding the delay in re-configuring many machines with the same configuration.</p>

<p><span class="UI_COMMAND" id="MenuBar_Empty_Tools.msg+MenuBar_Empty_Tools+7276">Configuration Manager</span> allows a centralized management of the application's configuration settings. If a application administrator creates a configuration, then other machines can upgrade during the program startup, automatically using the remote configuration behaviour.</p>

<table border="1" bordercolor="navy" bgcolor="#FFFFE1" cellpadding="10%" width="100%">
